ch/?P=MATH%20320" title="MATH 320" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MATH 320');">MATH 320</a></span></span> is required to obtain an endorsement in the teaching of math.</em></p></td></tr></table>
<h3>Minor in Mathematics</h3>
<p>A Minor in Mathematics requires MATH 180, MATH 181, and MATH 210 (already taken in the prerequisites for the Physics major) and 8 additional hours of MATH, MCS, or STAT electives at the 200-, 300-, or 400-level (with one in the MATH rubric with the exception of MATH 205).</p>
<p>To earn an endorsement in the teaching of math, students should complete the requirements for the Minor in Mathematics and the specific courses listed below.</p>
